IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. FILEMERGER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.

* This program merges two files into one. It reads records from
* two input files and writes them to an output file. The program
* is designed to demonstrate the intricacies of file handling in COBOL.
* It showcases the use of multiple variables and functions to achieve
* a seemingly simple task in a convoluted manner.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE1 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT1.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE2 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT2.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE1.
01  INPUT-RECORD1 PIC X(100).

FD  INPUT-FILE2.
01  INPUT-RECORD2 PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  EOF-FLAG1 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  EOF-FLAG2 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  TEMP-VAR1 PIC X(100).
01  TEMP-VAR2 PIC X(100).
01  TEMP-VAR3 PIC X(100).
01  TEMP-VAR4 PIC X(100).
01  FRODO PIC X(100).
01  SAM PIC X(100).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PARA.
    PERFORM INIT-PARA.
    PERFORM UNTIL EOF-FLAG1 = 'Y' AND EOF-FLAG2 = 'Y'
     PERFORM READ-FILE1
     PERFORM READ-FILE2
     PERFORM WRITE-OUTPUT
    END-PERFORM.
    PERFORM CLOSE-FILES.
    STOP RUN.

INIT-PARA.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE1
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE2
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE.

READ-FILE1.
    IF EOF-FLAG1 = 'N'
     READ INPUT-FILE1 INTO TEMP-VAR1
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO EOF-FLAG1
     NOT AT END
         MOVE TEMP-VAR1 TO FRODO
    END-IF.

READ-FILE2.
    IF EOF-FLAG2 = 'N'
     READ INPUT-FILE2 INTO TEMP-VAR2
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO EOF-FLAG2
     NOT AT END
         MOVE TEMP-VAR2 TO SAM
    END-IF.

WRITE-OUTPUT.
    IF EOF-FLAG1 = 'N'
     MOVE FRODO TO OUTPUT-RECORD
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-IF
    IF EOF-FLAG2 = 'N'
     MOVE SAM TO OUTPUT-RECORD
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-IF.

CLOSE-FILES.
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE1
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE2
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE.

